    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="80"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d80">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 493.11/538.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 3, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Lansing</hi>: You may be interested to know
                    that the contemplated action of the American Government in returning to China
                    the unused portion of the indemnity payments for the maintenance of the student
                    movement between China and the United States has called forth expressions of
                    gratitude from all quarters in Peking. I need hardly assure you that China will
                    never forget this generous act of the American Government. The provisions thus
                    made for the support of the Chinese students in this country are amply
                    sufficient for the next two years.</p>
                <p>With assurance [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kai Fu Shah</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
